This tome is old and fallen apart, but somehow, it feels like its not done sharing knowledge. Approaching it seems foolish, but perhaps worth the risk for those set out on a mission to delve deeper in the shadow arts?

Value.value: Blood and viscera, as well as the horrid stench of death drift down to you from a grated hole over your head.
The foul smells of gore, viscera, and death permeate this dark room. The dismembered corpses of several humanoid creatures hang from hooks and chains, as well as litter most surfaces.
You find your way to a mostly intact winding stairwell at what feels like the back of the ruins.

This room seems like a ruined version of some once great hall. The doors, columns, and statues are cracked and peeling. A heavy, oppressive gloom fills the air. Shadows gather thick in the corners and no light burns in the room.

As you approach this tome, the shadows fill your mind and soul. Nearly directly after this the effects of the shadow plane and magic in you are shown, your eyes flicker purple a moment. It's the presence of that energy showing through your eyes. You also feel drawn to a "island" outside this ruin..
